import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(10)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.bar(data['origin'], data['count'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What are the top 10 busiest airports in terms of number of flights?', wrap=True)
    for i in ax:
        plt.text(i.get_x() + i.get_width() / 2, i.get_height() + 10, str(i.get_height()), ha='center', va='bottom')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = pd.to_numeric(data['count'], errors='coerce')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['count'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of number of flights between airports?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['origin'] = data['origin'].astype('str')
    data['destination'] = data['destination'].astype('str')
    edges = data[['origin', 'destination']]
    edges = edges.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    G = nx.DiGraph()
    for idx, row in edges.iterrows():
        G.add_edge(row['origin'], row['destination'], weight=row['count'])
    pos = nx.spring_layout(G, k=0.5, iterations=50)
    edge_labels = {(i, j): f"{G[i][j]['weight']}" for i, j in G.edges()}
    nx.draw_networkx_edge_labels(G, pos, edge_labels=edge_labels, font_size=8)
    nx.draw(G, pos, node_size=1000, node_color='lightblue', with_labels=True, font_size=10, font_weight='bold')
    plt.title('What are the most popular routes in terms of number of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = pd.to_numeric(data['count'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['count'])
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.boxplot(data['count'])
    plt.title('What is the average number of flights per airport?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.axhline(data['count'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["count"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['origin'] = pd.to_datetime(data['origin'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['destination'] = pd.to_datetime(data['destination'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['origin'], data['count'])
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the correlation between distance and number of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
